subject: COM

sections.description: There are no classes for this section scheduled between June 3-11 due to the Congress of the Humanities and Social Sciences being held at UVic. The objective of this course is to give students a strategic vision and an in- depth knowledge of China --a rapidly developing and transforming economy. We pay special attention to cultural, political, and economic transformation of China. In particular, we will discuss Chinese culture and philosophies, middle class, Chinese currency fluctuation, Chinese stock and housing markets, population and sociology risks, energy risks, and marketing mix strategies in China. Our perspective is generally of the western business organization that wishes to exploit the opportunities afforded by remarkable growth of China.
